ntioned man helped commit the greatest scientific theft of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAtomic bombxHistoryxUnited States. 0aChemistszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiavBiography. 0aEspionage, SovietxHistoryxUnited States. 0aPrisonersxBiographyxPennsylvania. 0aSpiesxBiographyxUnited States. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Science & Technology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015678240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300156782423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300156782/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles